         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">8/3/95 ¶  ¶ Allow me, dear Prof Saccardo, to place before you the enclosed specimen for the valuable opinion of yours as that of a leading specialist. ¶  ¶ Would you find it possible to compile a Cens...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">95.03.08</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Pier Saccardo</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Orto Botanico, Università degli Studi, Padua.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">8/3/95</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Allow me, dear Prof Saccardo, to place before you the enclosed specimen for the valuable opinion of yours as that of a leading specialist.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Would you find it possible to compile a Census of Australian fungaceous plants in conformity with my Census of Vascular plants of Australia?<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">B89.12.03.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> You may be able to improve on what has been done by Dr Cooke in his special volume.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Cooke (1892).</p>
               </note> In 1896 the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">third</hi>
               </seg> Census is due,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The projected volume was never published.</p>
               </note> and I have asked now also Agardh, J. Mueller and Brotherus, whether they, — perhaps by the help of local University-Students would be able to put to gether such a list, so that the Evasculares could also appear in the Census of 1896. In your case your great work and Cooke's volume would need to be cited.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Most regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
